    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-21T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-21T09:00:00-05:00" n="279"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4218: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-21T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 21, 1941—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Your 84, April 16, 7 p.m. Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs yesterday
                    volunteered the information that he proposed to <pb facs="0341" n="333"
                        xml:id="pg_333"/> take up now in Washington the question of replacing the
                    Fiscal Representative by the Bank on the basis of the Department’s original
                        proposition.<note n="21" xml:id="d279fn21">See <ref
                            target="frus1936v05#pg_599">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1936, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, pp. 599</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I understand that Lescot proposes to present the problem of Haiti’s lack of
                    defense against external aggression. The Garde officers now accompanying him,
                    however, are believed to have been selected largely with a view to maintenance
                    of domestic <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> during his absence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
